column3:
Thank you Paper Magazine for this excellent interview with Vincent Martell, founder of VAM, director and co-writer of #DamagedGoods: 

&quot;I've never seen proper representation of myself as a gay, Black man. We were tired of waiting for people to figure it out, so we took matters into our own hands. The representation we have seen is plastic — based off a white, Hollywood perspective and not authentic or relatable. Growing up without any proper characters on TV to look up to can be detrimental to someone's psyche, and we're just now seeing a shift in Hollywood where the people behind the lens are also in front of the lens. There's power in that, and artists around the world can connect with these experiences.&quot; 

#DamagedGoods premieres on OTV on April 4!
